      "Crane mechanic retrieved from water",
      "Aircraft transported mechanic to medical facility",
      "BSEE onsite investigation conducted on October 16, 2023",
      "Personnel interviews conducted"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 13, 2023, at approximately 1745 hours, a crane mechanic fell approximately 96 feet from the gantry of a crane while attempting to remove a brace supporting exhaust muffler piping. The mechanic was not wearing a safety harness or life vest. When the second bolt broke during grinding operations, the mechanic was struck by the detached brace and fell over the handrail into the water. The mechanic suffered a fractured rib, dislocated shoulder, and internal bleeding.",
